  <constraints>
    <constraint>This task does NOT execute fixes — it validates that 032+033+034 produced the expected end-to-end behavior. If gaps remain, additional remediation tasks are filed.</constraint>
    <constraint>Solo SME stand-in mode: capture signoff verdict as "yes-with-conditions" max for Phase 1.5 acceptance; full credentialed legal-ops SME re-validation deferred to Phase 3 (task 044 lessons-learned + R6 backlog).</constraint>
    <constraint>NO-VERBATIM-CONTENT rule per ADR-018 + walkthrough doc top — paraphrase response text + citation excerpts; verbatim OK for question text, file names, correlationIds, signoff statement.</constraint>
    <constraint>Aggregate verdict ≥ 4/5 required to close Phase 2; ≥ 3/5 is "with conditions" (acceptable but file Sev-2 findings for R6); &lt; 3/5 = Sev-1 blocker, loop back.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <steps>
    <step>Verify 032+033+034 all deployed to Spaarke Dev (curl + visual check on SpaarkeAi shell).</step>
    <step>Pre-curl: `Authorization: Bearer notarealtoken` to `/api/ai/chat/sessions/{id}/summarize` and `/documents` — expect 401 (auth rejection at middleware), NOT "Tenant identity not found" detail (that detail is the bug we fixed mid-session).</step>
    <step>Open SpaarkeAi shell on Spaarke Dev (sprk_SpaarkeAi Code Page).</step>
    <step>Execute Phase A (Smoke) — should still pass.</step>
    <step>Execute Phase B (Direct /summarize) — the auto-trigger flow described in task prompt above.</step>
    <step>Execute Phase C (Multi-file convergence) — verify combined-summary interjection (FR-04) + multi-file output.</step>
    <step>Execute Phase D (Per-file affordance) — verify single-file Summarize from Context pane.</step>
    <step>Execute Phase E (Cap behavior) — verify 21st upload rejected with errorCode summarize.too-many-files.</step>
    <step>Fill per-phase checkboxes + verdict summary in task-030-summarize-walkthrough.md §3 + §4.</step>
    <step>Capture solo-SME signoff in §7 — record aggregate verdict 1-5 + verbatim signoff statement.</step>
    <step>If verdict ≥ 4/5: flip tasks 030, 031, 035 all to ✅ in TASK-INDEX.md. Update plan.md Phase 2 status to ✅.</step>
    <step>If verdict 3-3.9/5: flip task 030 ✅ with conditions; file Sev-2 findings as R6 backlog rows in §6 of walkthrough doc; flip 031 ✅; flip 035 ✅.</step>
    <step>If verdict &lt; 3/5: STOP. File new remediation tasks (036+). DO NOT close 030 or 031.</step>
  </steps>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>All 5 phases (A-E) executed; per-phase verdicts captured in walkthrough doc §3+§4.</criterion>
    <criterion>Operator-as-SME signoff captured verbatim in walkthrough doc §7.</criterion>
    <criterion>Aggregate Phase 1.5 verdict ≥ 4/5 — Summarize vertical works end-to-end without third-message ceremony.</criterion>
    <criterion>FR-01 convergence validated: at least one direct path AND one agent-tool path produce equivalent rendered output for the same uploaded file.</criterion>
    <criterion>FR-02 TL;DR-first streaming visible (TL;DR section renders before Summary section).</criterion>
    <criterion>FR-04 multi-file combined-summary interjection rendered verbatim in chat for ≥2 file uploads.</criterion>
    <criterion>NFR-02 20-file cap enforced gracefully (400 with stable errorCode).</criterion>
    <criterion>SC-08 byte-shape convergence: same prompt + same files via either path = same envelope shape.</criterion>
    <criterion>SC-18 SME signoff captured (solo stand-in mode, conditional on credentialed-SME re-validation in Phase 3 per spec §SC-18 phrasing).</criterion>
    <criterion>Tasks 030, 031, 035 all flipped ✅ in TASK-INDEX.md; Phase 2 closed in plan.md.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

